Usage:
Both utilities, czy and dzy take input from stdin, and output to stdout.

czy is used to compress and dzy is used to decompress.

Example usage:
echo "test message" | czy > output.txt
dzy < output.txt > decompressed.txt

Compressing the source of czy:
Original size: 4419 bytes.
Czy compressed size: 3547 bytes. Ratio:  .8027 (80.27%)
Gzip compressed size: 1524 bytes. Ratio: .3449 (34.49%)

Compressing the compiled czy binary:
